    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-12-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="732"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.42157SA29/1328½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-29">December 29,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>What has happened in regard to the old proposed Treaty with Canada<note n="74"
                        xml:id="d732fn74">
                        <ref target="frus1929v02#pg_94">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1929, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 94</ref>.</note> in regard to the use
                    of additional water at Niagara Falls? I think it was sent to the Senate by
                    President Hoover but died there. Will you speak to me about this when we take up
                    the St. Lawrence Treaty?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
